body.note:
The image-resolution is inheritable, so you can associate it on the root
      element. It does not apply on the page generated content (margin
      boxes).:root {
    image-resolution: 300dpi;
}To
      reset the image resolution to the one set in the image itself, you can use instead of a DPI
      value, the constant from-image:
      title:before {
    content: url("chapter-decorator.png");
    image-resolution: from-image;
}

To change the resolution for images that appear in a page margin box, set this property on
      that margin box, or directly on the @page rule, to apply to all page margin
      boxes:@page front-page {
    image-resolution: 600dpi;
}

@page {
    @top-center {
        image-resolution: 600dpi;
        content: url("company-logo.png");
    }
}
